    "extras": [
      "July to October is the easiest high-impact window: you get drier roads, Mara migration action, and generally clearer Kilimanjaro mornings in Amboseli, but Masai Mara fees are highest in that same period.",
      "January and February are the best value dry-season alternative if you want easier wildlife viewing without the July-December Mara fee spike and without the long rains.",
      "Safaricom is the most dependable SIM once you leave Nairobi; Airtel works in cities, but coverage becomes less predictable on safari drives and island transfers.",
      "Budget-to-mid safaris often bundle meals and game drives with the lodge, so compare package inclusions before judging a room rate in isolation.",
      "The SGR is the smoothest budget move between Nairobi and the coast, but if you are protecting a short trip, the Kenya Airways/Jambojet coastal hop saves half a day each way.",
      "Lamu and the safari circuit both reward light packing: many camps and island guesthouses handle luggage better when you keep to a soft duffel rather than a rigid suitcase."
    ],
